The paper deals with the optimization of Age-of-Information (AoI) in information-update systems, which is a topic related to networked systems and information theory. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely categories. The paper also introduces a new Pull model and discusses the tradeoff between different levels of information freshness and response times, which can be seen as a control and optimization problem in systems and control theory, leading to the possibility of cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a likely category. The paper also discusses the utility maximization problem, which can be seen as a machine learning and optimization problem, leading to the possibility of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely categories.
